description: A scaled-down version of the ceremony celebrating the Isle of Man's national day will be held on 6 July.
title: Coronavirus: Tynwald Day pared back due to social distancing
title_page: Coronavirus: Tynwald Day pared back due to social distancing - BBC News
maintext: In a pared back version of the proceedings, members of Tynwald will be joined by the Lieutenant Governor on Tynwald Hill, the judiciary will be represented by the island's First Deemster and the Lord Bishop of Sodor and Man will represent the church.
